## 1. Overview / Genel

This Terms of Use file describes how BlossomVale may be used, redistributed, credited, and what liabilities the author disclaims. Code is licensed under the included `LICENSE` (MIT). Non-code assets bundled with releases (textures, icons, sounds, models, etc.) are licensed under `ASSETS-LICENSE.md` (recommended: CC‑BY‑4.0). See those files for full legal texts.

Bu belge, BlossomVale modunun kullanım, yeniden dağıtım ve atıf kurallarını ile yazarın sorumluluk reddini açıklar. Kod için `LICENSE` (MIT) dosyasına, varlıklar için `ASSETS-LICENSE.md` dosyasına bakınız.

---

## 2. Attribution / Atıf (Lütfen Uyun)

When distributing the mod, including it in a modpack, or showing it in public media (videos/streams), please include one of the following attribution lines:

- Distribution / Modpack / Web pages:
  "BlossomVale — by Cat_YaraliKomutan (https://github.com/catyaralikomutan) — Assets CC‑BY‑4.0, Code MIT."

- Video / Stream description (YouTube preferred tag):
  "Mod: BlossomVale by Cat_YaraliKomutan — https://github.com/catyaralikomutan — Please credit the author and tag https://www.youtube.com/@Cat_YaraliKomutan"

- In‑game / credits:
  "BlossomVale — created by Cat_YaraliKomutan"

Varlıkları değiştirdiyseniz, değişiklikleri belirtin (ör. "Modified from original by [your name]"). CC‑BY‑4.0 şartlarına uyunuz.

Note: Requesting a YouTube tag is a preferred/standard attribution request — include the channel link above in video descriptions or tags where possible. Requiring social-media tagging as a strict legal condition is difficult to enforce; still, please respect and follow this attribution in practice.

---

## 3. Permissions & Restrictions / İzinler ve Sınırlamalar

- Code: Licensed under MIT (`LICENSE`) — you may use, modify, distribute, and include in commercial works provided the original copyright and license notice remain.
- Assets: Licensed as described in `ASSETS-LICENSE.md` (recommended CC‑BY‑4.0) — attribution is required.
- If you want to use this mod or its assets in a commercial product or paid bundle, please contact the author for written permission at the GitHub Issues link below or via other contact methods.

